--- body ---
## Context

`scripts/_divergence_semantic.py` imports a subset of helpers from
`_divergence_io`:

```python
from _divergence_io import (
    get_min_papers,
    per_window_year_ranges,
    subsample_equal_n,
)
```

But the module also calls `empty_divergence_df()` at four sites in the
empty-results guard paths:

- L226 (S1 MMD)
- L307 (S2 energy distance)
- L365 (S3 sliced Wasserstein)
- L502 (S4 Frechet)

`empty_divergence_df` is not in the import block, so any guard that fires
will raise `NameError: name 'empty_divergence_df' is not defined` instead
of returning the empty schema-correct DataFrame the dispatcher expects.

This is latent — none of the smoke fixtures currently exercise these
guards, so tests pass. It will fire on real corpora with windows where
`_iter_window_pairs` yields nothing (gap config, min_papers filter, or
subsample failures eliminate all pairs).

The bug is pre-existing — it was introduced in PR#764 alongside the
guards, but the import was not updated. PR#778 (ticket 0120) fixed the
analogous gap in `_divergence_citation`, `_divergence_community`,
`_divergence_lexical`, and `_divergence_c2st` but explicitly scoped
`_divergence_semantic` out (PR#778 review thread, 2026-05-01).

## Fix

Single-line change to the import block in `scripts/_divergence_semantic.py`:

```python
from _divergence_io import (
    empty_divergence_df,
    get_min_papers,
    per_window_year_ranges,
    subsample_equal_n,
)
```

## Test

Add a unit test (or extend an existing one) that constructs a fixture
where `_iter_window_pairs` yields nothing, calls one of S1-S4, and
asserts the returned DataFrame has the schema columns and zero rows.
The pattern is already in place for the other 4 modules — copy from
`tests/test_*_empty_corpus_dispatcher_guard*.py` or wherever ticket
0121 landed.

## Exit criteria

- `empty_divergence_df` imported in `_divergence_semantic.py`.
- Unit test exercises at least one of the four guard sites
  (L226, L307, L365, L502) with an empty windows fixture.
- `make check-fast` green.

## Risk

Trivial. One import line + one test. No behaviour change in any
non-empty path.
